minicp.state

Interface StateMap<K,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    K - the key type
    V - the value type
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CopyMap, TrailMap

    public interface StateMap<K,V>
    A generic map that can revert its state with StateManager.saveState() / StateManager.restoreState() methods.
    See Also:
    for the creation.

      • put

        void put(K k,
         V v)
        Inserts the key-value pair. It erases the existing ones if the map already contains an entry with the given key.
        Parameters:
        k - the key
        v - the value

        V get(K k)
        Retrieves the value for a given key.
        Parameters:
        k - the key
        Returns:
        the value v if the entry (k,v) was previously put, null otherwise
